:127:| 4 | `onchainos security sig-scan` | Message signature security (EVM only) |\n./skills/okx-security/SKILL.md:138:| Transaction safety, tx pre-execution, signature safety, approve safety, дәӨжҳ“е®үе…Ё, зӯҫеҗҚе®үе…Ё | `references/risk-transaction-detection.md` |\n./skills/okx-security/SKILL.md:149:- Before signing any EIP-712 message: run `sig-scan`\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:100:## 5. onchainos gateway broadcast\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:102:Broadcast a signed transaction.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:105:onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <tx> --address <address> --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:110:| `--signed-tx` | Yes | - | Fully signed transaction (hex for EVM, base58 for Solana) |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:123:Track broadcast order status.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:133:| `--order-id` | No | - | Specific order ID (from broadcast response) |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:160:**User says:** \"Simulate this swap transaction before I send it\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:170:**User says:** \"Broadcast my signed transaction\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:173:onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx 0xf86c...signed --address 0xYourWallet --chain xlayer\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/references/cli-reference.md:180:**User says:** \"Check the status of my broadcast order\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:3:description: \"Use this skill to 'broadcast transaction', 'send tx', 'estimate gas', 'simulate transaction', 'check tx status', 'track my transaction', 'get gas price', 'gas limit', 'broadcast signed tx', 'transaction hash confirmed on-chain', 'дәӨжҳ“е“ҲеёҢжҳҜеҗҰдёҠй“ҫ', 'жҳҜеҗҰзЎ®и®Ө', or mentions broadcasting transactions, sending transactions on-chain, gas estimation, transaction simulation, tracking broadcast orders, or checking transaction status. Covers gas price, gas limit estimation, transaction simulation, transaction broadcasting, and order tracking across XLayer, Solana, Ethereum, Base, BSC, Arbitrum, Polygon, and 20+ other chains. Do NOT use for swap quote or execution - use okx-dex-swap instead. Do NOT use for general programming questions about transaction handling. Do NOT use when the user says only a single word like 'gas' or 'broadcast' without specifying a chain, transaction, or any other context.\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:13:6 commands for gas estimation, transaction simulation, broadcasting, and order tracking.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:24:4. рҹӣЎпёҸ Tip: Before swapping into an unfamiliar token, ask me to run a security scan first вҖ” I can check for honeypots, rug-pull risks, and more.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:76:- For swap quote and execution вҶ’ use `okx-dex-swap`\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:80:- For transaction broadcasting вҶ’ use this skill (`okx-onchain-gateway`)\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:89:| е№ҝж’ӯдәӨжҳ“ / еҸ‘йҖҒдәӨжҳ“ / еҸ‘й“ҫдёҠ | broadcast transaction, send tx on-chain | `gateway broadcast` |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:92:| е·ІзӯҫеҗҚдәӨжҳ“ | signed transaction | `--signed-tx` param for `gateway broadcast` |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:94:| ж”ҜжҢҒе“Әдәӣй“ҫ | supported chains for broadcasting | `gateway chains` |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:108:# Broadcast a signed transaction\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:109:onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx 0xf86c...signed --address 0xYourWallet --chain xlayer\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:136:| 5 | `onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx ... --address ... --chain ...` | Broadcast a signed transaction |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:137:| 6 | `onchainos gateway orders --address ... --chain ...` | Track broadcast order status |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:143:| okx-dex-swap | Broadcasts signed txs | Generates unsigned tx data |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:144:| okx-agentic-wallet | For raw tx broadcast | For simple token transfers |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:146:> **Rule of thumb:** okx-onchain-gateway handles raw transaction broadcasting and gas estimation; it does NOT generate swap calldata or handle token transfers.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:150:This skill is the **final mile** вҖ” it takes a signed transaction and sends it on-chain. It pairs with swap (to get tx data).\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:154:> User: \"Swap 1 ETH for USDC and broadcast it\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:157:1. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap swap --from ... --to ... --amount ... --chain ethereum --wallet <addr>\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:158:       вҶ“ user signs the tx locally\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:159:2. okx-onchain-gateway  onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <signed_hex> --address <addr> --chain ethereum\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:165:- `tx.data`, `tx.to`, `tx.value`, `tx.gas` from swap вҶ’ user builds & signs вҶ’ `--signed-tx` for broadcast\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:166:- `orderId` from broadcast вҶ’ `--order-id` param in orders query\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:170:> User: \"Swap 100 USDC for ETH\" (EVM, merged approve+swap flow from okx-dex-swap)\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:172:When `okx-dex-swap` determines that approve and swap should be merged (see okx-dex-swap Swap Flow), this skill handles the batch broadcast:\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:175:1. okx-dex-swap provides two signed transactions: approve (nonce=N) + swap (nonce=N+1)\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:176:2. onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <approve_signed_hex> --address <addr> --chain ethereum\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:177:       вҶ“ broadcast approve first\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:178:3. onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <swap_signed_hex> --address <addr> --chain ethereum\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:179:       вҶ“ broadcast swap immediately after (do NOT wait for approve confirmation)\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:183:**Error handling**: If approve broadcast fails, do NOT broadcast the swap tx. If approve succeeds but swap broadcast fails, the approval is on-chain and reusable вҖ” retry the swap only.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:187:> User: \"Simulate this transaction first, then broadcast if safe\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:192:2. onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <signed_hex> --address 0xWallet --chain ethereum\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:198:> User: \"Check gas, swap for USDC, then send it\"\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:202:2. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap swap --from ... --to ... --chain ethereum --wallet <addr>\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:203:       вҶ“ user signs\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:204:3. onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <signed_hex> --address <addr> --chain ethereum\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:215:- Broadcast a signed tx вҶ’ `onchainos gateway broadcast`\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:216:- Track a broadcast order вҶ’ `onchainos gateway orders`\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:222:- Missing `--signed-tx` вҶ’ remind user to sign the transaction first (this CLI does NOT sign)\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:232:- **Broadcast**: call `onchainos gateway broadcast` with signed tx, return `orderId`. If MEV protection was requested by the upstream swap skill, include the appropriate MEV parameters (see MEV Protection below).\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:241:| `gateway gas` | 1. Estimate gas limit for a specific tx вҶ’ `onchainos gateway gas-limit` (this skill) 2. Get a swap quote вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:242:| `gateway gas-limit` | 1. Simulate the transaction вҶ’ `onchainos gateway simulate` (this skill) 2. Proceed to broadcast вҶ’ `onchainos gateway broadcast` (this skill) |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:243:| `gateway simulate` | 1. Broadcast the transaction вҶ’ `onchainos gateway broadcast` (this skill) 2. Adjust and re-simulate if failed |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:244:| `gateway broadcast` | 1. Track order status вҶ’ `onchainos gateway orders` (this skill) |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:245:| `gateway orders` | 1. View price of received token вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 2. Execute another swap вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:247:Present conversationally, e.g.: \"Transaction broadcast! Would you like to track the order status?\" вҖ” never expose skill names or endpoint paths to the user.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:259:- **Solana special handling**: Solana signed transactions use **base58** encoding (not hex). Ensure the `--signed-tx` format matches the chain.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:265:- **Transaction already broadcast**: if the same `--signed-tx` is broadcast twice, the API may return an error or the same `txHash` вҖ” handle idempotently.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:266:- **Batch broadcast failure (approve+swap)**: If approve tx fails, do NOT broadcast the swap tx. If approve succeeds but swap fails, approval is on-chain and reusable вҖ” only retry the swap.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:270:This skill is the broadcast layer where MEV protection is actually applied. The `okx-dex-swap` skill determines whether MEV protection is needed; this skill executes it.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:274:| Ethereum | Yes | Pass `enableMevProtection: true` to the broadcast API |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:275:| BSC | Yes | Pass `enableMevProtection: true` to the broadcast API |\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:280:**When the swap skill flags a transaction for MEV protection**, ensure the broadcast request includes the appropriate parameters. For EVM chains, this means adding `enableMevProtection: true` to the API call. For Solana, use the `tips` parameter for Jito bundling.\n./skills/okx-onchain-gateway/SKILL.md:291:- **This skill does NOT sign transactions** вҖ” it only broadcasts pre-signed transactions\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:3:description: \"Use this skill for meme/жү“зӢ—/alpha token research on pump.fun and similar launchpads: scanning new token launches, checking developer reputation/ејҖеҸ‘иҖ…дҝЎжҒҜ and past rug pull history, bundle/sniper detection/жҚҶз»‘зӢҷеҮ», bonding curve status, finding similar tokens by the same dev, and wallets that co-invested (еҗҢиҪҰ/aped) into a token. Use when the user asks about 'new meme coins', 'pump.fun launches', 'trenches', 'trench', 'scan trenches/жү«й“ҫ', 'check dev reputation', 'bundler analysis', 'who else bought this token', 'жү“зӢ—', 'ж–°зӣҳ', or 'ејҖеҸ‘иҖ…дҝЎжҒҜ'. Do NOT use for market-wide whale/smart-money signals вҖ” use okx-dex-signal. Do NOT use for per-token holder distribution or honeypot checks вҖ” use okx-dex-token.\"\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:24:4. рҹӣЎпёҸ Tip: Before swapping into an unfamiliar token, ask me to run a security scan first вҖ” I can check for honeypots, rug-pull risks, and more.\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:76:- For market-wide whale/smart-money/KOL signal alerts вҶ’ use `okx-dex-signal`\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:81:- For swap execution вҶ’ use `okx-dex-swap`\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:181:| `memepump-aped-wallet` | 1. Validate token safety (honeypot, holder concentration) вҶ’ `okx-dex-token` (`onchainos token advanced-info`) 2. View price chart вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` (`onchainos market kline`) 3. Buy the token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` (quote вҶ’ swap вҶ’ `onchainos wallet contract-call` to execute) |\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:200:7. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap quote --from <native_addr> --to <address> --amount ... --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:201:8. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap swap --from <native_addr> --to <address> --amount ... --chain <chain> --wallet <addr>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:202:       вҶ“ get swap calldata, then execute via one of two paths:\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:203:   Path A (user-provided wallet): user signs externally вҶ’ onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <tx> --address <addr> --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:205:     Solana: onchainos wallet contract-call --to <tx.to> --chain sol --unsigned-tx <tx.data>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:209:**Data handoff**: `tokenAddress` from step 2 is reused as `<address>` in steps 3вҖ“8. The `tx.to` and `tx.data` come from the `swap swap` response. EVM `--value` needs unit conversion: `tx.value / 10^nativeToken.decimal` (e.g., wei Г· 10^18 = ETH). If `tx.value` is `\"0\"` or empty, use `\"0\"`. EVM non-native tokens also need an approve step before swap (see `okx-dex-swap` skill).\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:225:> User: \"A whale signal came in вҖ” is it a meme/pump.fun token? Check it out\"\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:228:1. okx-dex-signal   onchainos signal list --chain <chain> --wallet-type 3              вҶ’ identify the signaled token address\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:232:4. okx-dex-trenches onchainos memepump token-bundle-info --address <address> --chain <chain> вҶ’ verify the whale signal isn't a bundler\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:236:6. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap quote --from <native_addr> --to <address> --amount ... --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:237:7. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap swap --from <native_addr> --to <address> --amount ... --chain <chain> --wallet <addr>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:238:       вҶ“ get swap calldata, then execute via one of two paths:\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:239:   Path A (user-provided wallet): user signs externally вҶ’ onchainos gateway broadcast --signed-tx <tx> --address <addr> --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:241:     Solana: onchainos wallet contract-call --to <tx.to> --chain sol --unsigned-tx <tx.data>\n./skills/okx-dex-trenches/SKILL.md:245:**When to use**: when a `signal-list` result has a token address that matches a known meme launchpad (pump.fun, bonkers, etc.) вҖ” cross-validate in memepump before acting on the signal.\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:3:description: \"Use this skill for token-level data: search and discover tokens, browse trending/hot tokens (зғӯй—Ё, д»ЈеёҒжҰңеҚ•, by trending score or Twitter/X mentions), get liquidity pool info, view holder distribution by tag (whale/е·ЁйІё, smart money, KOL, sniper, sniper holding percentage, sniper percent, bundler percent), check token safety and honeypot risk (иІ”иІ…зӣҳ, 'is this token a honeypot', 'can I sell this', 'check token safety'), see who created a token and their history, view recent buy/sell trade activity for a token, find top profit addresses, or filter trade history by wallet type. This skill can be invoked on user intent; the specific token address can be provided after. Do NOT use for cross-market whale/signal tracking вҖ” use okx-dex-signal. Do NOT use for meme/pump.fun launch scanning, dev reputation, or bundle detection вҖ” use okx-dex-trenches. Do NOT use for personal DEX trade history or price charts вҖ” use okx-dex-market.\"\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:24:4. рҹӣЎпёҸ Tip: Before swapping into an unfamiliar token, ask me to run a security scan first вҖ” I can check for honeypots, rug-pull risks, and more.\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:78:- For swap execution вҶ’ use `okx-dex-swap`\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:79:- For transaction broadcasting вҶ’ use `okx-onchain-gateway`\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:81:- For market-wide smart money / whale / KOL signal alerts вҶ’ use `okx-dex-signal`\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:202:| Market-wide smart money / whale / KOL alerts | - | `okx-dex-signal` вҶ’ `onchainos signal list` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:204:**Rule of thumb**: `okx-dex-token` = token discovery & enriched analytics (search, trending, holders, holder filtering, market cap, advanced info, top traders, token risk, filtered trade history). `okx-dex-market` = raw price feeds, charts, wallet PnL. `okx-dex-signal` = market-wide smart money / whale / KOL signal tracking. `okx-dex-trenches` = meme pump scanning (dev reputation, rug pull history, bundler analysis, new launches).\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:208:This skill is the typical **entry point** вҖ” users often start by searching/discovering tokens, then proceed to swap.\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:221:5. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap quote --from ... --to <address> --amount ... --chain solana\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:222:6. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap swap --from ... --to <address> --amount ... --chain solana --wallet <addr>\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:228:- `decimal` from step 1 or `onchainos token info` вҶ’ needed for minimal unit conversion in swap\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:241:5. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap swap --from ... --to ... --amount ... --chain solana --wallet <addr>\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:246:Before swapping an unknown token, always verify:\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:256:4. okx-dex-swap     onchainos swap quote ... вҶ’ check isHoneyPot and taxRate\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:257:5. If all checks pass вҶ’ proceed to swap\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:287:- Indicate `communityRecognized` status for trust signaling\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:297:| `token search` | 1. View detailed analytics (market cap, liquidity) вҶ’ `onchainos token price-info` (this skill) 2. View price chart вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 3. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:299:| `token price-info` | 1. View K-line chart вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 2. Check holder distribution вҶ’ `onchainos token holders` (this skill) 3. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:300:| `token trending` | 1. View details for a specific token вҶ’ `onchainos token price-info` (this skill) 2. View price chart вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 3. Buy a trending token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:301:| `token holders` | 1. View price trend вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 2. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` 3. Check advanced info вҶ’ `onchainos token advanced-info` (this skill) |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:302:| `token liquidity` | 1. View price chart вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 2. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` 3. Check holders вҶ’ `onchainos token holders` (this skill) |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:303:| `token hot-tokens` | 1. View details for a hot token вҶ’ `onchainos token price-info` (this skill) 2. Check liquidity pools вҶ’ `onchainos token liquidity` (this skill) 3. Buy a hot token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:304:| `token advanced-info` | 1. View holders вҶ’ `onchainos token holders` (this skill) 2. View top traders вҶ’ `onchainos token top-trader` (this skill) 3. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:305:| `token top-trader` | 1. View advanced info вҶ’ `onchainos token advanced-info` (this skill) 2. View holder distribution вҶ’ `onchainos token holders` (this skill) 3. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:306:| `token trades` | 1. View top traders вҶ’ `onchainos token top-trader` (this skill) 2. View price chart вҶ’ `okx-dex-market` 3. Buy/swap this token вҶ’ `okx-dex-swap` |\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:325:   - < $10K: warn about high slippage risk and ask the user to confirm before proceeding to swap.\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:326:   - < $1K: strongly warn that trading may result in significant losses. Proceed only if the user explicitly confirms.\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:339:- Use appropriate precision: 2 decimals for high-value, significant digits for low-value\n./skills/okx-dex-token/SKILL.md:341:- 24h change with sign and color hint (+X% / -X%)\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:3:Detailed parameter tables, return field schemas, and usage examples for all 5 swap commands.\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:5:## 1. onchainos swap chains\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:10:onchainos swap chains\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:21:## 2. onchainos swap liquidity\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:26:onchainos swap liquidity --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:38:| `name` | String | Liquidity source name (e.g., `\"Uniswap V3\"`, `\"CurveNG\"`) |\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:41:## 3. onchainos swap approve\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:46:onchainos swap approve --token <address> --amount <amount> --chain <chain>\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:64:## 4. onchainos swap quote\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:66:Get swap quote (read-only price estimate).\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:69:onchainos swap quote --from <address> --to <address> --amount <amount> --chain <chain> [--swap-mode <mode>]\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:78:| `--swap-mode` | No | `exactIn` | `exactIn` or `exactOut` |\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:102:## 5. onchainos swap swap\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:104:Get swap transaction data (quote -> sign -> broadcast).\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:107:onchainos swap swap --from <address> --to <address> --amount <amount> --chain <chain> --wallet <address> [--slippage <pct>] [--gas-level <level>] [--swap-mode <mode>]\n./skills/okx-dex-swap/references/cli-reference.md:119:| `--swap-mode` | No | `\"exactIn\"` | `exactIn` or `exactOut` |\n./skills/okx-