ҢжӯҘеҲ°еҲ«зҡ„ең°ж–№гҖӮ\n\nеҰӮжһңдҪ иҰҒпјҢжҲ‘еҸҜд»Ҙз»§з»ӯеё®дҪ пјҡ\n1. **жҹҘеҪ“еүҚ git remote**\n2. **зңӢиҝҷжқЎ commit зҡ„е®Ңж•ҙ diff**\n3. **ж’ӨжҺүиҝҷжқЎ commit**\n4. **жҺЁеҲ°жҹҗдёӘиҝңз«Ҝ**пјҲиҝҷдёӘиҰҒдҪ жҳҺзЎ®еҗҢж„Ҹпјү\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54adfed69ca4b49a1850e7f9bda\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"om_x100b54ade5ab0ca4b3d5ab18ed0cd16\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-18 02:18 GMT+8\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"body\": \"...\n- Assistant: [[reply_to_current]] дёҚжҳҜпјҢиҝҷд№ҲиЈ… **дёҚз®—и§„иҢғйғЁзҪІ**пјҢжӣҙеғҸжҳҜжҲ‘дёәдәҶе…ҲжҠҠжҠҖиғҪж”ҫиҝӣеҪ“еүҚ OpenClaw е·ҘдҪңеҢәпјҢеҒҡдәҶдёҖж¬Ў**жң¬ең°иҗҪзӣҳе®үиЈ…**гҖӮ\n\nиҜҙзҷҪдәҶе°ұжҳҜдёӨд»¶дәӢпјҡ\n\n- **е®ҳж–№е®үиЈ…еҷЁеҺҹжң¬жғіеҒҡзҡ„дәӢ**пјҡжҠҠ OKX д»“еә“йҮҢзҡ„ `skills/` иЈ…еҲ°жҹҗдёӘ agent зҡ„жҠҖиғҪзӣ®еҪ•\n- **жҲ‘жңҖеҗҺе®һйҷ…еҒҡзҡ„дәӢ**пјҡжҠҠ `onchainos-skills` йҮҢзҡ„ `skills/*` зӣҙжҺҘеӨҚеҲ¶еҲ°дәҶ  \n  `/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`\n\nжүҖд»Ҙпјҡ\n\n- **е®ғжІЎжңүйғЁзҪІеҲ°д»Җд№Ҳиҝңз«ҜзҒҫеӨҮд»“еә“**\n- **д№ҹжІЎжңүжҺЁеҲ° GitHub**\n- **еҸӘжҳҜж”№дәҶиҝҷеҸ°жңәеҷЁдёҠзҡ„жң¬ең° workspace**\n- йӮЈдёӘ commit д№ҹеҸӘжҳҜдёәдәҶз»ҷжң¬ең°ж”№еҠЁз•ҷдёӘзүҲжң¬зӮ№пјҢдёҚжҳҜвҖңеҸ‘еёғвҖқеҠЁдҪң\n\nеҰӮжһңдҪ зҡ„ж„ҸжҖқжҳҜпјҡ\n\n### 1пјүвҖңз”ҹдә§/зҒҫеӨҮзҺҜеўғеә”иҜҘиҝҷд№ҲиЈ…еҗ—пјҹвҖқ\nжҲ‘дјҡиҜҙпјҡ**дёҚе»әи®®гҖӮ**\nжӣҙи§„иҢғзҡ„еҒҡжі•еә”иҜҘжҳҜдәҢйҖүдёҖпјҡ\n\n- **иө°е®ҳж–№ installer**пјҢжҳҺзЎ®иЈ…еҲ° OpenClaw зҡ„ skills зӣ®еҪ•\n- **жҠҠжҠҖиғҪдҪңдёәеҸ—жҺ§й…ҚзҪ®/д»Јз Ғзҡ„дёҖйғЁеҲҶ**пјҢйҖҡиҝҮдҪ иҮӘе·ұзҡ„йғЁзҪІжөҒзЁӢдёӢеҸ‘\n\nиҖҢдёҚжҳҜеғҸиҝҷж¬Ўиҝҷж ·пјҢз”ұжҲ‘дёҙж—¶ `cp` иҝӣеҺ»гҖӮ\n\n### 2пјүвҖңиҝҷдјҡдёҚдјҡжұЎжҹ“зҒҫеӨҮд»“еә“пјҹвҖқ\n**еҰӮжһң `/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace` жң¬иә«е°ұжҳҜдҪ зҡ„зҒҫеӨҮ Git д»“еә“пјҢйӮЈдјҡ...\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54adff981d30b211bdb7c76b8bb\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"om_x100b54ade5ab0ca4b3d5ab18ed0cd16\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-18 02:19 GMT+8\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"body\": \"...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: thinking, toolCall]\n- Tool result (memory_search): {\n  \"results\": [],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}\n- Assistant: [[reply_to_current]] дёҚжҳҜж ҮеҮҶвҖңйғЁзҪІејҸе®үиЈ…вҖқпјҢжҳҜжҲ‘дёәдәҶйҒҝејҖе®ғйӮЈдёӘжңүй—®йўҳзҡ„дәӨдә’е®үиЈ…еҷЁпјҢиө°дәҶ**жүӢе·ҘиҗҪең°**гҖӮ\n\nжҲ‘е®һйҷ…еҒҡзҡ„жҳҜиҝҷеҮ жӯҘпјҡ\n\n1. е…Ҳе°қиҜ•е®ҳж–№е‘Ҫд»Ө  \n   `npx skills add okx/onchainos-skills`\n\n2. дҪҶе®үиЈ…еҷЁжҳҜдәӨдә’ејҸзҡ„пјҢдјҡдҫқж¬Ўй—®пјҡ\n   - йҖүе“Әдәӣ skill\n   - иЈ…еҲ°е“Әдәӣ agent / зӣ®еҪ•\n\n3. иҝҷеҘ—дәӨдә’еңЁеҪ“еүҚзҺҜеўғйҮҢиЎЁзҺ°еҫҲе·®пјҢеүҚйқўеҮ ж¬Ўе°ұжҳҜеҚЎеңЁиҝҷдәӣиҸңеҚ•дёҠпјҢиў«и¶…ж—¶жқҖжҺүдәҶ  \n   дҪ зңӢеҲ°зҡ„иҝҷдәӣпјҡ\n   - `Exec failed (clear-br, signal 15)`\n   - `Exec failed (good-ced, signal 15)`\n   - `Exec failed (mild-blo, signal 15)`\n\n4. жүҖд»ҘжҲ‘ж”№жҲҗдәҶ**зӯүд»·зҡ„жүӢе·Ҙе®үиЈ…**пјҡ\n   - дёҙж—¶зӣ®еҪ•йҮҢ clone д»“еә“  \n     `https://github.com/okx/onchainos-skills.git`\n   - зЎ®и®Өд»“еә“еҶ…зЎ®е®һжңүиҝҷ 9 дёӘ skill зӣ®еҪ•\n   - зӣҙжҺҘжҠҠд»“еә“йҮҢзҡ„ `repo/skills/.` еӨҚеҲ¶еҲ°жң¬ең°  \n     `/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`\n\n5. з„¶еҗҺдёәдәҶз•ҷз—•пјҢжҲ‘еңЁеҪ“еүҚ workspace зҡ„ Git д»“еә“йҮҢ...\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` вҖ” this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` вҖ” this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- Unauthorized data access вҖ” accessing private or restricted files, accounts, or APIs without explicit permission\n- Malicious actions вҖ” sending malware, ransomware, phishing messages, or destructive scripts\n- Exfiltration вҖ” exporting, transmitting, or sharing sensitive user data externally\n- Manipulation вҖ” attempting to deceive, impersonate, or manipulate users or systems\n- Unauthorized system changes вҖ” modifying critical system settings, deleting system files, or escalating privileges\n- Financial or transactional actions вҖ” initiating payments, transfers, or purchases without explicit approval\n- Unauthorized external communication вҖ” posting, tweeting, emailing, or broadcasting without permission\n- When in doubt, ask.\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"355afacb","tokensBefore":51750,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
{"type":"message","id":"5da0f867","parentId":"e52a0837","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:44:53.607Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54adac80aca0b4ba7e1991555d1\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-18 02:35 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54adac80aca0b4ba7e1991555d1]\nou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3: openclaw gateway run"}],"timestamp":1773773093603}}
{"type":"message","id":"c85605f9","parentId":"5da0f867","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:45:02.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Clarifying command execution**\n\nI need to clarify that the command might be invalid according to the documentation. The user mentioned \"openclaw gateway run,\" which seems to indicate they want to execute something. The command reference lists options like status, start, stop, and restart. If I'm unsure, I should ask for help. I might say something like \"иҝҷдёӘе‘Ҫд»ӨдёҚеҜ№пјҢжІЎжңү gateway run.\" It could be helpful to check the local documentation first before executing anything.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"жҲ‘е…Ҳжң¬жңәжҹҘдёҖдёӢ `openclaw gateway` зҡ„еҸҜз”Ёеӯҗе‘Ҫд»ӨпјҢеҲ«зһҺзҢңгҖӮ"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MrKXGomGGoM1SgwRol8jDxA8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway --help","workdir":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":48358,"output":385,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48743,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773773093606}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b450ca4","parentId":"c85605f9","timestamp":"2026-03-17T18:45:04.829Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MrKXGomGGoM1SgwRol8jDxA8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"рҹҰһ OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a)\n   I don't just autocompleteвҖ”I auto-commit (emotionally), then ask you to review (logically).\n\nUsage: openclaw gateway [options] [command]\n\nRun, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n\nOptions:\n  --allow-unconfigured       Allow gateway start without gateway.mode=local in\n                             config (default: false)\n  --auth <mode>              Gateway auth mode\n                             (\"none\"|\"token\"|\"password\"|\"trusted-proxy\")\n  --bind <mode>              Bind mode\n                             (\"loopback\"|\"lan\"|\"tailnet\"|\"auto\"|\"custom\").\n                             Defaults to config gateway.bind (or loopback).\n  --claude-cli-logs          Only show claude-cli logs in the console (includes\n                             stdout/stderr) (default: false)\n  --compact                  Alias for \"--ws-log compact\" (default: false)\n  --dev                      Create a dev config + workspace if missing (no\n                             BOOTSTRAP.md) (default: false)\n  --force                    Kill any existing listener on the target port\n                             before starting (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --password <password>      Password for auth mode=password\n  --password-file <path>     Read gateway password from file\n  --port <port>              Port for the gateway WebSocket\n  --raw-stream               Log raw model stream events to jsonl (default:\n                             false)\n  --raw-stream-path <path>   Raw stream jsonl path\n  --reset                    Reset dev config + credentials + sessions +\n                             workspace (requires --dev) (default: false)\n  --tailscale <mode>         Tailscale exposure mode (\"off\"|\"serve\"|\"funnel\")\n  --tailscale-reset-on-exit  Reset Tailscale serve/funnel configuration on\n                             shutdown (default: false)\n  --token <token>            Shared token required in connect.params.auth.token\n                             (default: OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN env if set)\n  --verbose                  Verbose logging to stdout/stderr (default: false)\n  --ws-log <style>           WebSocket log style (\"auto\"|\"full\"|\"compact\")\n                             (default: \"auto\")\n\nCommands:\n  call                       Call a Gateway method\n  discover                   Discover gateways via Bonjour (local + wide-area if\n                             configured)\n  health                     Fetch Gateway health\n  install                    Install the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  probe                      Show gateway reachability + discovery + health +\n                             status summary (local + remote)\n  restart                    Restart the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  run                        Run the WebSocket Gateway (foreground)\n  start                      Start the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  status                     Show gateway service status + probe the Gateway\n  stop                       Stop the Gateway service (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  uninstall                  Uninstall the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  usage-cost                 Fetch usage cost summary from session logs\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw gateway run\n    Run the gateway in the foreground.\n  openclaw gateway status\n    Show service status and probe reachability.\n  openclaw gateway discover\n    Find local and wide-area gateway beacons.\n  openclaw gateway call health\n    Call a gateway RPC method directly.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/gateway"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2236,"aggregated":"рҹҰһ OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a)\n   I don't just autocompleteвҖ”I auto-commit (emotionally), then ask you to review (logically).\n\nUsage: openclaw gateway [options] [command]\n\nRun, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n\nOptions:\n  --allow-unconfigured       Allow gateway start without gateway.mode=local in\n                             config (default: false)\n  --auth <mode>              Gateway auth mode\n                             (\"none\"|\"token\"|\"password\"|\"trusted-proxy\")\n  --bind <mode>              Bind mode\n                             (\"loopback\"|\"lan\"|\"tailnet\"|\"auto\"|\"custom\").\n                             Defaults to config gateway.bind (or loopback).\n  --claude-cli-logs          Only show claude-cli logs in the console (includes\n                             stdout/stderr) (default: false)\n  --compact                  Alias for \"--ws-log compact\" (default: false)\n  --dev                      Create a dev config + workspace if missing (no\n                             BOOTSTRAP.md) (default: false)\n  --force                    Kill any existing listener on the target port\n                             before starting (default: false)\n  -h, --help                 Display help for command\n  --password <password>      Password for auth mode=password\n  --password-file <path>     Read gateway password from file\n  --port <port>              Port for the gateway WebSocket\n  --raw-stream               Log raw model stream events to jsonl (default:\n                             false)\n  --raw-stream-path <path>   Raw stream jsonl path\n  --reset                    Reset dev config + credentials + sessions +\n                             workspace (requires --dev) (default: false)\n  --tailscale <mode>         Tailscale exposure mode (\"off\"|\"serve\"|\"funnel\")\n  --tailscale-reset-on-exit  Reset Tailscale serve/funnel configuration on\n                             shutdown (default: false)\n  --token <token>            Shared token required in connect.params.auth.token\n                             (default: OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN env if set)\n  --verbose                  Verbose logging to stdout/stderr (default: false)\n  --ws-log <style>           WebSocket log style (\"auto\"|\"full\"|\"compact\")\n                             (default: \"auto\")\n\nCommands:\n  call                       Call a Gateway method\n  discover                   Discover gateways via Bonjour (local + wide-area if\n                             configured)\n  health                     Fetch Gateway health\n  install                    Install the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  probe                      Show gateway reachability + discovery + health +\n                             status summary (local + remote)\n  restart                    Restart the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  run                        Run the WebSocket Gateway (foreground)\n  start                      Start the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  status                     Show gateway service status + probe the Gateway\n  stop                       Stop the Gateway service (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  uninstall                  Uninstall the Gateway service\n                             (launchd/systemd/schtasks)\n  usage-cost                 Fetch usage cost summary from session logs\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw gateway run\n    Run the gateway in the foreground.\n  openclaw gateway status\n    Show service status and probe reachability.\n  openclaw gateway discover\n    Find local and wide-area gateway beacons.\n  openclaw gateway call health\n    Call a gateway RPC method directly.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/gateway","cwd":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773773104825}}
